      &= m(a + g \sin \theta) \\
      &= (1.0)\left(1 + 9.8 \times 0.5\right) \\
      &= 5.9 \, \text{N} \quad (\theta = 30^\circ)
\end{align*}

\subsection*{(ii) Equation of Motion: Down the Incline}

The equation of motion for an object moving down an incline is given by:

\begin{equation}
    ma = F + mg \sin \theta
\end{equation}

Solving for \( F \):

\begin{align*}
    F &= ma - mg \sin \theta \\
      &= m(a - g \sin \theta) \\
      &= (1.0)\left(1 - 9.8 \times 0.5\right) \\
      &= -3.9 \, \text{N}
\end{align*}

The negative sign implies that the force \( F \) is to be applied up the incline.

